<item>
            <title>[HIVE-9234] HiveServer2 leaks FileSystem objects in FileSystem.CACHE</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-9234</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Running over extended period (48+ hrs), we&apos;ve noticed HiveServer2 leaking FileSystem objects in FileSystem.CACHE. Linked jiras were previous attempts to fix it, but the issue still seems to be there. A workaround is to disable the caching (by setting &lt;tt&gt;fs.hdfs.impl.disable.cache&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;fs.file.impl.disable.cache&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;true&lt;/tt&gt;), but creating new FileSystem objects is expensive.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
